<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
By its large size and distinctive coloration (infuscate wings; black body and legs, with only abdomen apically pale), 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pampsilota afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pampsilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The coloration of the abdomen varies from the described typical (darker) form to the apical half of the abdomen yellow-orange with terga 5/6 medially more or less black. In these pale specimens sterna 2-4 are basally yellow-orange. This form with a more or less entirely yellow-orange apical half of abdomen was described under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pampsilota afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<normalizedToken originalValue="maynéi">maynei</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
Forsius, 1928. Other morphological differences to the nominate form are not detectable. The holotype (MRAC) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pampsilota afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<normalizedToken originalValue="maynéi">maynei</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
was not examined, but the paratype seems to have been collected on the same date and at the same place as the holotype, and there is no reason to doubt that the specimens are conspecific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
